reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Had Doubts, But Happy with my Purchase
reviews.reviewText: I had doubts as reviews were negative about the zipper, smell, & durability. I bought 2 of the 20" suitcase and each was used as a carry-on for 4 different plane rides and I love this luggage! The outer shell is a little flexible so it is more forgiving on packing your clothes. Packed full was still lightweight enough to lift in the overhead compartment on the plane. Zippers inside & out functioned fine. All 4 wheels rolled fine on concrete or asphalt, but on carpet it worked better pulling suitcase on 2 wheels. The retractable handle worked fine, but on the flimsy side when on all 4 wheels. However, reasonable price.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 6, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Cheap but rather durable
reviews.reviewText: I needed a carry-on bag for a trip and landed on this one based on the price and size, which perfectly fit Delta's carry-on size restrictions. You can tell from certain aspects like the zipper and material that it's a cheaper product, but it's not noticeable unless you're paying close attention. All-in-all, it did exactly what I needed it to do for a good price and hasn't failed me yet.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 7, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars GOOD for the price
reviews.reviewText: Is it the smoothest roll? No. Does it have the sturdiest design? No. Is it a GREAT deal for the price? YES. It doesn't feel high quality because it is not. BUT it has given us a surprisingly good performance. It survived an airline trip and 4-5 road trips already. No tears, zippers still work good. Long term we like to invest in a little nicer luggage. But when we need something last minute I would 100% buy again!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 22, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Moves very easy
reviews.reviewText: Love the color, very packable. Fits a lot for size. Perfect for over head storage on plane

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 24, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars This little baby did not disappoint!!
reviews.reviewText: Some of the reviews gave me pause, many said they were careful to not over pack, so I thought I'd have to be very careful as well. Let me tell you, I packed this suitcase full and it held it shape and zipped with ease. No bulge! Light weight, very functional. The wheels glide smoothly. I'm so glad I got it. It was very inexpensive, but I feel like it will last for years and hold up well.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 12, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Durable luggage and roomy!
reviews.reviewText: So much room in the luggage! There is the two sides for your belongings and one side has a zipper to separate things if needed. did not have any issue with it being carry on size. I bought two different colors the colors were spot on what I ordered. Will purchase the same when it’s time for another.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 4, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Light but cheap
reviews.reviewText: You get what you pay for- a poor quality lightweight suitcase.Pros: love the color, love how lightweight it isCons: poor quality. Janky zipper, even more janky extendable handle, scratches like crazyI got this carry on for a 10 day trip. By day 1, the suitcase had scratches. By day 3, the extendable handle was already not working. By end of trip, the zipper was already getting stuck while zipping up the corners and already seeing weak points in places. The quality of the hard case in general feels very cheap, but I guess that's what you get for having it lightweight. Recommend for very light trips. Definitely personally handle it, not sure if it would survive getting checked in.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 1, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars As expected and is a pretty color
reviews.reviewText: Am happy with the purchase. I chose a used-like new option and it really looked unused. Maybe a tiny touch of dirt on the handle. Still smelled new. Like other reviews the quality is not great, but it should get the job done. I have not used it yet so if something happens I’ll come back and edit my review, but for my used version I paid $25 so I think it was worth it even if it only lasts a couple trips!

reviews.reviewTitle: Spinner carry on great for travel
reviews.reviewText: Purchased the navy hard sided spinner travel in case for an overseas vacation . Worked great . Loved the spinner wheels , the navy colour was easy to spot . Great quality , excellent price

I purchased the set of 2 about 4 weeks ago. It arrived well packaged with a gift of lady speed stick deodorant inside the luggage.I went on vacation with the bigger one last week and I came back with it intact. This product is really worth the money. Light weight, spacious and it rolls well.For me, it is a good deal.

I have already taken it on 10 flights and it still looks and works like new. The common complain seems to be the handle but I would say that it probably feels weaker than it actually is.Zero issues so far. I was expecting it to already fall apart for this price.It fits more than you think and is very light. The shell itself is not super thick, so if you’re packing a lot of stuff and can’t close it - I wouldn’t recommend doing any manoeuvres which involve pressing on it with your knee.
